{
  "texts": [
    "We show that our measure, generated using data only from before the patent was granted, strongly predicts the estimated patent values.",
    "Our commercial potential measure also predicts patent value controlling for factors such as patent class (CPC), the number of scientific papers a patent builds upon, and the number of future patent citations it receives. foot_11",
    "A limitation of these validation exercises is that they test the measure against patent citations, proxies for firms' beliefs about commercializability.",
    "In this section, we test the measure against outcomes marking the progression of science through a major university's technology transfer process that reflect university and firm decisions about commercializability.",
    "Providing detailed information from a major university's technology transfer office (TTO), the dataset encompasses all invention disclosures and subsequent actions and outcomes, including patenting, licensing, agreements, revenue, TTO investments per invention, licensee type (startup or established firm),"
  ]
}